May 5, 1929 D Nambour Contest (Oval March)
Nambour Contest (Oval March) 100 March Contest Nambour Contest nambour-contest-oval-march
Nambour, Queensland, Australia See http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/21403532
Run under a handicap system, whereby the scores of the Apple Tree Creek, Nambour, and Kandanga bands were each increased by 8 points. Only playing was judged, not marching.
Supplementary information from Dennis Mitchell, son of David Mitchell.
Nov. 15, 2011, 11:46 a.m. Nov. 15, 2011, 12:43 p.m.
1 Apple Tree Creek Citizens Brass Band David Mitchell March: Victoria
2 Nambour Town Band P. Harrison March: First Parade
3 Kandanga District Unknown March: Knight of the Road
4 Windsor Municipal Unknown March: Challenge
5 Gympie City Band Unknown March: The Victor's Return
